wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Anko Project: Professional Accounting Ecosystem Website

## Project Introduction

**Anko** is a comprehensive professional accounting ecosystem website designed for "   " (Accounting Ecosystem Association). The project serves as a modern, responsive platform providing business accounting services, educational programs, and professional support services to entrepreneurs in Novorossiysk, Russia.

### Purpose Statement
The platform aims to deliver professional accounting services including business registration, tax compliance, financial reporting, and educational support through an intuitive web interface with administrative capabilities.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- Provide comprehensive business accounting and legal support services
- Offer educational programs and training for entrepreneurs
- Deliver professional team support with expert guidance
- Enable efficient client management and communication
- Maintain high security standards with JWT authentication

### Target Audience
- Small and medium business owners in Novorossiysk
- Entrepreneurs seeking professional accounting services
- Business consultants and legal advisors
- Educational institutions supporting business development

## Technical Architecture

The Anko project follows a modern full-stack architecture with clear separation between frontend and backend components.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Client Browser] --> B[React Frontend]
    B --> C[Express.js Backend API]
    C --> D[MongoDB Database]
    C --> E[Authentication Layer]
    E --> F[JWT Token Management]
    
    G[Admin Panel] --> B
    H[PWA Features] --> B
    I[Static Content] --> B
    
    subgraph "Frontend Layer"
        B
        G
        H
        I
    end
    
    subgraph "Backend Layer"
        C
        E
        F
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        D
    end
```

### Component Breakdown

**Frontend Architecture:**
- React 19 with TypeScript for type-safe development
- Vite for fast development and building
- React Router DOM for client-side routing
- Tailwind CSS for responsive styling
- PWA (Progressive Web App) support for offline functionality

**Backend Architecture:**
- Express.js RESTful API
- MongoDB with Mongoose ODM
- JWT-based authentication system
- Multer for file uploads
- Helmet for security headers
- Morgan for HTTP logging

### Design Patterns

The project implements several key design patterns:

- **Context Pattern**: For global state management (AuthContext, DataContext)
- **Provider Pattern**: For dependency injection and state sharing
- **Repository Pattern**: For data access abstraction
- **Middleware Pattern**: For request/response processing
- **Factory Pattern**: For component creation and configuration

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points

**Frontend Entry Point:**
- `src/App.tsx` - Main application component with routing configuration
- `src/index.tsx` - React application bootstrap
- `vite.config.ts` - Vite build configuration with PWA support

**Backend Entry Point:**
- `server/server.js` - Express server configuration and route definitions
- `server/server-new.js` - Alternative server implementation

### Core Modules

**Authentication System:**
- `src/context/AuthContext.tsx` - Centralized authentication state management
- `server/middleware/auth.js` - JWT authentication middleware
- `server/utils/jwt.js` - JWT token utilities

**Data Management:**
- `src/context/DataContext.tsx` - Global data state management
- `server/db/in-memory.js` - In-memory database simulation
- `src/types.ts` - TypeScript interfaces and type definitions

**Content Management:**
- `server/routes/content.js` - Content CRUD operations
- `server/routes/media.js` - Media file management
- `server/models/` - Data model definitions

### Configuration Approach

**Environment Configuration:**
- `.env` - Local development environment variables
- `.env.example` - Environment variable template
- `netlify.toml` - Netlify deployment configuration

**Build Configuration:**
- `vite.config.ts` - Vite build optimization and PWA settings
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript compilation settings
- `postcss.config.js` - PostCSS processing configuration

### External Dependencies

**Frontend Dependencies:**
- `react` ^19.2.4 - Core React library
- `react-router-dom` ^7.13.0 - Client-side routing
- `lucide-react` ^0.563.0 - Icon library
- `axios` ^1.13.5 - HTTP client for API requests

**Backend Dependencies:**
- `express` ^4.18.2 - Web application framework
- `mongoose` ^8.23.0 - MongoDB object modeling
- `jsonwebtoken` ^9.0.2 - JWT token handling
- `bcryptjs` ^2.4.3 - Password hashing

### Integration Points

**API Integration:**
- RESTful endpoints for all CRUD operations
- JWT authentication for protected routes
- File upload handling via Multer
- Real-time data synchronization

**External Services:**
- Google Fonts for typography
- Cloudinary for image optimization
- Netlify for static hosting
- GitHub Actions for CI/CD pipeline

### Component Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[App Component] --> B[Layout Component]
    A --> C[ErrorBoundary]
    A --> D[AuthProvider]
    A --> E[DataProvider]
    
    B --> F[Navigation]
    B --> G[Main Content]
    
    D --> H[AuthContext]
    E --> I[DataContext]
    
    H --> J[ProtectedRoute]
    I --> K[Content Components]
    
    subgraph "State Management"
        H
        I
    end
    
    subgraph "UI Components"
        F
        G
        J
        K
    end
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview

**Public Website Features:**
- Responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Multi-language support (Russian interface)
- SEO optimization with meta tags
- Social media integration
- Contact form with validation

**Administrative Features:**
- Role-based access control (admin-only)
- Content management system
- User administration
- Media gallery management
- Client relationship management

**Technical Features:**
- Progressive Web App (PWA) support
- Offline functionality
- Performance optimization
- Security best practices
- Automated testing suite

### Implementation Highlights

**Performance Optimization:**
- Code splitting with React.lazy
- Image optimization with optimized images
- Service worker caching
- Bundle splitting for vendor libraries

**Security Implementation:**
- JWT-based authentication
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- CORS configuration
- Helmet security headers
- Rate limiting middleware

**Testing Strategy:**
- Unit testing with Vitest
- End-to-end testing with Playwright
- Component testing with React Testing Library
- Continuous integration pipeline

### Feature Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unauthenticated
    Unauthenticated --> Authenticating: Login Attempt
    Authenticating --> Authenticated: Valid Credentials
    Authenticating --> Unauthenticated: Invalid Credentials
    Authenticated --> AdminPanel: Admin Access
    Authenticated --> PublicWebsite: Regular User
    AdminPanel --> ContentManagement: Manage Content
    AdminPanel --> UserManagement: Manage Users
    AdminPanel --> MediaManagement: Manage Media
    PublicWebsite --> ContactForm: Submit Inquiry
    PublicWebsite --> ServicePages: View Services
    PublicWebsite --> TeamDirectory: View Team
    PublicWebsite --> NewsSection: View News
    PublicWebsite --> FAQSection: View FAQ
    
    AdminPanel --> Unauthenticated: Logout
    PublicWebsite --> Unauthenticated: Logout
```

The Anko project represents a well-architected full-stack application that effectively combines modern frontend technologies with robust backend services to deliver a comprehensive business accounting ecosystem platform. The modular architecture ensures maintainability and scalability while the comprehensive feature set addresses the diverse needs of both clients and administrators.

**Sources:**

- [server/package.json](server/package.json)
- [src/App.tsx](src/App.tsx)
- [server/server.js](server/server.js)
- [vite.config.ts](vite.config.ts)
- [src/context/AuthContext.tsx](src/context/AuthContext.tsx)
- [src/pages/admin/AdminLayout.tsx](src/pages/admin/AdminLayout.tsx)
- [server/routes/content.js](server/routes/content.js)
- [server/db/in-memory.js](server/db/in-memory.js)
- [playwright.config.ts](playwright.config.ts)
- [src/context/DataContext.tsx](src/context/DataContext.tsx)
- [src/types.ts](src/types.ts)
- [docker-compose.yml](docker-compose.yml)
- [.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml](.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml)

</blog>
